---
alwaysApply: true
---

# Zoho Project Coding Rules

This project uses a centralized design system (ODS).
These rules are MANDATORY and apply to every page in the project.

---

## Design System Imports (REQUIRED on every page)

Every HTML page MUST import two CSS files in this exact order:

1. **`design-system/ods-design-system.css`** — Zoho-wide tokens, semantics, and components.
2. **`design-system/themes/<product>.css`** — the product theme matching this project's product (e.g. `shift.css`, `crm.css`, `books.css`).

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="design-system/ods-design-system.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="design-system/themes/shift.css">
```

Never reverse the order — the theme depends on the base.

---

## Semantic vs Raw Tokens

The design system defines two layers of CSS variables. **Always prefer semantic tokens.**

### Semantic tokens (use these)

Express design intent — what a value is FOR.

| Token | What it's for |
|---|---|
| `var(--cta)` | Primary CTA fill — ODS blue, same on every Zoho product |
| `var(--cta-hover)`, `var(--cta-active)`, `var(--cta-focus)` | CTA states |
| `var(--canvas)` | Page background, default surface |
| `var(--brand)` | Product brand color (banners, accents, links) — varies per product |
| `var(--brand-hover)` | Hover state for brand surfaces |
| `var(--secondary)` | Dark theme section background |
| `var(--fg-primary)` | Headlines |
| `var(--fg-secondary)` | Sub-headlines |
| `var(--fg-tertiary)` | Body paragraphs |
| `var(--fg-muted)` | Decorative / disabled — fails 4.5:1, never readable text |
| `var(--success)`, `var(--warning)`, `var(--error)`, `var(--info)` | Status colors |
| `var(--line)` | Card borders, neutral strokes |
| `var(--line-active)` | Active flow paths, focus borders |
| `var(--light-gradient-top)`, `var(--light-gradient-bottom)` | Light banner gradient stops |

### Raw tokens (use only when no semantic name exists)

Express what a value IS — a specific shade.

| Pattern | Example |
|---|---|
| `var(--color-<family>-<shade>)` | `var(--color-orange-300)` for a specific accent |
| `var(--<scale>-<shade>)` (from product theme) | `var(--primary-700)`, `var(--gray-400)`, `var(--slate-500)` |
| `var(--space-<size>)` | `var(--space-md)` |
| `var(--radius-<size>)` | `var(--radius-sm)` |

Reach for raw tokens only when you need a specific shade and no semantic name covers your case.

---

## Hard Rules

- Use ONLY CSS variables defined by the design system (semantic OR raw).
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or font sizes.
- The `design-system/` folder is READ-ONLY.
- If a token is missing, ASK before creating one.
- **CTA fill is always `var(--cta)`** (ODS blue). Never use `var(--brand)` on a button — that's a hard violation. The brand color is for surfaces, not CTAs.

---

## Figma to Code Rules

This project follows strict Figma-to-code implementation rules.

### General

- Always inspect Figma layer names before writing HTML.
- Semantic correctness is mandatory.
- Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA) is mandatory.

---

## HTML Rules

1. **Layer name → semantic element.** If a Figma layer name exactly matches a
   semantic HTML element (`span`, `ul`, `li`, `small`, `label`), you MUST use
   that HTML element.

   ```
   Layer name "span" → <span>content</span>
   ```

2. **`zwc-` prefix → class name, not element.** Layer names starting with
   `zwc-` represent CLASS NAMES, never HTML elements.

   ```
   zwc-banner-wrap → <div class="zwc-banner-wrap">
   ```

3. **No `<div>` when a semantic element is appropriate.** Use `section`,
   `header`, `nav`, `main`, `article`, `footer`, `ul`, `li`, `p`, etc. wherever
   the content calls for them.

4. **No purposeless class names.** Avoid patterns like `<p class="banner-para">`.
   Scope styles using the parent section class instead.

---

## Section Structure (MANDATORY)

Every section MUST follow this exact structure:

```html
<section class="zwc-section-name">
  <div class="content-wrap">
    <div class="inner-content">
      <!-- section content -->
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

Rules:

- Every section MUST include `content-wrap`.
- `content-wrap` controls `max-width` ONLY.
- `inner-content` is used for spacing and layout.
- Do NOT apply `padding`, `gap`, or `flex` on `content-wrap`.

---

## CSS Rules

- Do NOT use `!important`.
- Do NOT write inline styles.
- Do NOT use the universal selector (`*`).
- Do NOT write styles directly on HTML tags. Always scope styles under a
  parent class.
- Do NOT add common styles to `body` (no `font-size`, `color`, `line-height`,
  `spacing`).
- Do NOT use `<br>` tags for spacing.
- Do NOT add unnecessary animations or transitions.

---

## Layout Rules

- Use ONLY `display: flex` for layouts.
- Do NOT use `grid`, position-based layouts, or `float`.

---

## Typography

- Do NOT use `font-weight` directly.
- Always use predefined font-family variables from the design system.

---

## Images

- Banner images MUST use `fetchpriority="high"`.
- Non-critical images MUST use `loading="lazy"`.
- Always specify `width` and `height`.
- Always provide meaningful `alt` text.

---

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML is mandatory.
- ARIA attributes must be added where required.
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines strictly.
